      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations via Method of Manufactured Solutions (MMS) or equivalent benchmark for rotating-frame Navier-Stokes. Gradation 2: published benchmark comparison sufficient.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent has been verified against the FDA critical path benchmark (pipe flow and nozzle) published in Hariharan et al. (2011). Internal MMS results for the k-omega SST turbulence closure available in solver theory manual. Verification evidence accepted at Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence study required with GCI < 5% on primary QoI. Gradation 2 minimum; Gradation 3 achieved through formal Richardson extrapolation with asymptotic range confirmation.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh Richardson extrapolation performed (4.2M / 11.6M / 28.9M cells). GCI_fine = 1.8% on impeller-outlet shear-stress scalar. Asymptotic range confirmed (GCI_ratio = 1.03). Exceeds MRL 2 requirement; Gradation 3 assigned."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must match COU operating envelope within documented tolerances. Gradation 2: conditions documented and overlap demonstrated.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro loop tests conducted at 2.5, 5.0, 7.5 L/min and 2000, 2500, 3000 RPM. COU operating envelope spans 2.5–7.5 L/min and 1800–3200 RPM. Overlap confirmed. Temperature (37 ± 0.5 °C) and blood analog viscosity (3.5 ± 0.2 cP) documented in test report TR-2023-04."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric defined; model predictions compared to experimental data with error norms reported. Gradation 2: point-wise comparison with documented error metric.",
      "rationale": "RH ratio and NIH values compared at all five validation operating points. RMS error 9.3%; maximum point error 14.8% at 2.5 L/min / 3000 RPM. Error within pre-specified ±15% acceptance band. Comparison documented in validation report VR-2023-07."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoIs must be directly traceable to the COU decision QoIs. Gradation 2: direct mapping documented.",
      "rationale": "COU decision QoI is relative hemolysis index RH. Validation QoI is NIH computed from the same Giersiepen scalar transport model and normalized identically. Direct one-to-one mapping documented in credibility assessment plan CAP-2023-01."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must address the same physics regime and device geometry as the COU. Gradation 2: same device family with documented geometric and flow similarity.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump, which is the same geometry used in the COU. Flow regime (Re ~12,000–35,000; turbulent rotating-frame) is identical. Blood analog (glycerin-water, viscosity matched) used in lieu of whole blood per standard FDA guidance; documented justification in CAP-2023-01 §4.3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, Gradation 1 (acknowledgment of potential solver errors) is sufficient if discretization error is formally quantified.",
      "rationale": "Solver error not separately quantified. Discretization error formally bounded via GCI (see Discretization Error factor). Iterative convergence monitored: all residuals below 1e-5; mass imbalance < 0.01%. Gradation 1 accepted at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, Gradation 1 acknowledged. Formal use-error analysis not required.",
      "rationale": "Simulation executed by credentialed CFD engineer with 8 years rotodynamic pump experience. Peer review of simulation setup performed by independent analyst. No formal use-error FMEA conducted; Gradation 1 accepted at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model and turbulence closure selection must be justified for the COU physics. Gradation 2: literature-supported justification with sensitivity check on closure choice.",
      "rationale": "k-omega SST selected for adverse pressure gradient and rotating-frame flows per Menter (1994) and FDA benchmark studies. Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model selected per established literature (Zhang et al. 2011). Sensitivity analysis comparing SST vs. realizable k-epsilon showed <3% difference in NIH at worst-case point. Model form uncertainty estimated at ±12% based on inter-model spread."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs (geometry, boundary conditions, material properties) must be documented with sources and uncertainties. Gradation 2: inputs documented with nominal values and uncertainty ranges.",
      "rationale": "Pump geometry from FDA benchmark CAD file (public release v1.2). Inlet flow rate uncertainty ±5%; rotational speed uncertainty ±2%; blood viscosity 3.5 ± 0.3 cP. All inputs tabulated in simulation data package SDP-2023-02. Sensitivity of NIH to input perturbations quantified via one-at-a-time analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, Gradation 1 is acceptable. Sample-to-sample variability acknowledgment sufficient.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro tests used single pump specimen from FDA benchmark program. Sample-to-sample geometric variability not characterized. Acknowledged as limitation; Gradation 1 accepted at MRL 2 per CAP-2023-01 §5.2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
